In his first publication about the new fracture plane-related IFF criteria,14 Puck has extensively discussed the general shape of the experimentally well captured (σ2,τ21)-fracture curve (cp. Figure 4) and the basic observations associated with the occurring fracture plane orientations. These observations led to the distinction of three different sections of the fracture curve. Starting from σ2=R⊥ t, via τ21=R⊥‖ and ending at σ2=-R⊥ c (cp. Figure 4), there consecutively occur different stress combinations on the fracture plane leading to different modes of IFF (Table 2).
